Three years ago, the Nets pulled off a deal that one high-ranking front office member called “transformative.” Now, in the wake of Kevin Durant’s trade demand and Kyrie Irving’s broken relationship with the team, the Nets have become a cautionary tale about the risks of superstar empowerment. A trainwreck. One of the most disappointing teams in recent NBA history. Nets general manager Sean Marks and owner Joe Tsai took a huge gamble in putting this team together, and lost.